From: R9700 team <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: 2026-05-08
Subject: [PATCH] gemma4_causal: drop dual-EntryClass that collides with gemma4_mm

Patch 001 (`rdna4-upstream-sync`) introduces a stub
`Gemma4ForConditionalGeneration(Gemma4ForCausalLM): pass` and registers it
via `EntryClass = [Gemma4ForCausalLM, Gemma4ForConditionalGeneration]` at
the bottom of `gemma4_causal.py`.  In v0.5.11 `gemma4_mm.py:120` ALSO
defines + registers `Gemma4ForConditionalGeneration` (the real multimodal
implementation, `EntryClass = Gemma4ForConditionalGeneration` at
`gemma4_mm.py:906`).

Two registrations for the same name → model registry asserts at import
time:

  AssertionError: Duplicated model implementation for
                  Gemma4ForConditionalGeneration

Surfaces on every model launch (registry init runs at import, so this
blocks Gemma 4 AND every other model from coming up).  Discovered
2026-05-08 during R9700 hardware launch test.

This patch removes the stub class + reverts `EntryClass` back to the
single-value `Gemma4ForCausalLM` form (matches upstream v0.5.11).  The
multimodal `gemma4_mm.py` registration becomes the canonical
`Gemma4ForConditionalGeneration`.  Same shape as 3090's old patch 022,
which v0.5.11 already accepted upstream — R9700's patch 001 just needed
to drop its local override.

Receipt: scripts/eval/validate_capabilities.py 3/3 PASS on
Qwen3-VL-32B-AWQ-balanced post fix.

diff --git a/python/sglang/srt/models/gemma4_causal.py b/python/sglang/srt/models/gemma4_causal.py
--- a/python/sglang/srt/models/gemma4_causal.py
+++ b/python/sglang/srt/models/gemma4_causal.py
@@ -1053,10 +1053,4 @@
         return loaded_params


-# Text-only alias for multimodal architecture name
-# Allows loading Gemma4ForConditionalGeneration models without vision
-class Gemma4ForConditionalGeneration(Gemma4ForCausalLM):
-    pass
-
-
-EntryClass = [Gemma4ForCausalLM, Gemma4ForConditionalGeneration]
+EntryClass = Gemma4ForCausalLM
